en_7816986_0	Colombo (News 1st): The Annual Sri Lanka Cricket Awards 2018/19 was held in Colombo last night (December 03).
en_7816986_1	A large number of current and former Sri Lankan cricketers were present at the awards ceremony held at Battaramulla.
en_7816986_2	The awards ceremony was filled with many colourful entertainment items.
en_7816986_3	Mickey Arthur, Grant Flower and Shane McDermott, the newly appointed coaching panel of the Sri Lanka cricket team, were also present at the event.
en_7816986_4	Dhananjaya de Silva, who won the Test Batsman of the Year award last year, was adjudged the best Test batsman this year and Dimuth Karunaratne the current test and ODI captain won the Test Batsman of the year award.
en_7816986_5	Dilruwan Perera was adjudged the Best Test bowler of the year.
en_7816986_6	Pathum Nissanka won the Emerging Cricketer of the Year award, Kusal Janith Perera won the best ODI batsman of the year and Lasith Malinga won both the Best ODI bowlers award.
en_7816986_7	Thisara Perera won the Best All-rounder’s award.
en_7816986_8	Isuru Udana was named the Best T20I All-rounder and Thisara Perera also bagged the T20 batsman of the year.
en_7816986_9	It is noteworthy that Lasith Malinga won a hat-trick of best T20 bowler of the year award.
en_7816986_10	Kumar Dharmasena was unanimously named the Best International Umpire of the Year for the 2nd consecutive year.
en_7816986_11	Chamari Atapattu won the Best T20 & ODI batter, Best ODI all-rounder of the Year in women’s category, while Oshandi Ranasinghe won the best ODI bowler.
en_7816986_12	Shashikala Siriwardane bagged the women’s T20 bowler and the best All-rounder of the year awards.
en_7816986_13	Sri Lanka women’s cricket sensation Chamari Atapattu was named as the Women’s Cricketer of the Year.
en_7816986_14	However, it is noteworthy that the coveted cricketer of the year award was not presented this year.
